This move isn't remotely related of &quot;getting back&quot; to the US, but creating a more stable economic environment for ourselves. The EU is accepting new members again in 2008, and I expect us to join this time (we said no in 72 and 94). Russia, the worlds 2nd largest oil exporter, is also getting increasingly tied to europe and it's entirely likely they'll use euro as well. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
